This file contains list of all available parameters and the default
values used by Events Menu definition file.

This file IS NOT loaded by engine and should not be used as-is.
It's meant to be a reference for adding parameters to your own events.def file.

 ____________________
/       EVENTS       \_____________________________________________________

Load event assets.
Event items added are displayed in: Extras - Events submenu.

Setup following parameters below "[Event <0...>]" section:

- id = text
Set to name that should be returned by GameMode trigger.
This parameter also initiates new events declaration, so it has to be
assigned before any other parameter used by the same event.
All events should have unique id names.

- info = text
Set the info text that should be displayed for an event unlocked.

- previewspr = <groupNo,indexNo>
Set groupNo and indexNo to read from sprite file defined in
"eventSpr" events.lua file, to show sprite preview for item.

- previewpos = <posX,posY>
Set posX and posY to sprite preview defined in "eventSpr" events.lua file.

- previewscale = <scaleX,scaleY>
Set scaleX and scaleY to sprite preview defined in "eventSpr" events.lua file.

- path = path.lua
Path to file with lua extension (relative to game directory)
containing event mode custom fight coded in Lua language.

- unlock
Pure Lua code, executed exactly as is, each time upon loading events menu
and after complete one. If it evaluates to boolean 'true' the event
will be selectable from events mode submenu, or locked on 'false'.
Default: true.

- time = local/net
Set time that will be considered to check the event available time.
Only local or net(internet) time are available.

- yearstart = 20XX
Sets the year in which the event will be Available.

- yeardeadline = 20XX
Sets the year in which the event will be Unavailable.

- monthstart = Jan/Feb/Mar/Apr/May/Jun/Jul/Aug/Sep/Oct/Nov/Dec
Sets the month in which the event will be Available.
Month's name must be abbreviated to be recognized.

- monthdeadline = Jan/Feb/Mar/Apr/May/Jun/Jul/Aug/Sep/Oct/Nov/Dec
Sets the month in which the event will be Unavailable.
Month's name must be abbreviated to be recognized.

- daystart = 1/30
Sets the day in which the event will be Available.

- daydeadline = 1/30
Sets the day in which the event will be Unavailable.

- hourstart = 00/23
Sets the hour in which the event will be Available.
Only military format is supported.

- hourdeadline = 00/23
Sets the hour in which the event will be Unavailable.
Only military format is supported.

- minutestart = 00/59
Sets the minute in which the event will be Available.

- minutedeadline = 00/59
Sets the minute in which the event will be Unavailable.

- secondstart = 00/59
Sets the second in which the event will be Available.

- seconddeadline = 00/59
Sets the second in which the event will be Unavailable.

;---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Some Examples:

[Event 1]
id = event1
info = Trouble Dude
previewspr = 0,1
path = data/events/event1.lua
time = local
;Event Start Available at this Time!
monthstart = Oct
hourstart = 13
;Event Deadline at this Time!
monthdeadline = Nov
hourdeadline = 23

[Event 2]
id = event2
info = All-Star Match 1
previewspr = 0,2
previewpos = 20,60
previewscale = 0.5,0.8
path = data/events/event2.lua
unlock = stats.modes ~= nil and stats.modes.event ~= nil and stats.modes.event.event1 ~= nil and stats.modes.event.event1.clear == true
time = net
monthstart = Jun
monthdeadline = Sep